===Etymology 1===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|ar|فَتْحَة||an [[opening]]}}, {{ar-instance noun|nocat=1|lc=1}} of the verb {{m|ar|فَتَحَ||to [[open]]}}. Refers to the mouth position when pronuncing the {{IPAchar|/a/}} vowel.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|en|fatḥa}}, {{l|en|fatHa}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/fɑːt.hɑ/}}

====Noun====
{{examples|{{l|ar||دَ}}:&nbsp; {{IPAchar|/da/}}.<br> {{l|ar||دَا}} or {{l|ar||دَى}}:&nbsp; {{IPAchar|/daː/}}}}
{{en-noun}}

# In [[Arabic]] [[script]], the [[vowel]] point for ''[[a]]'', appearing as a [[diagonal]] [[line]] placed above a letter (&thinsp;[[َ|{{lang|ar|ـَ}}]]&thinsp;) and designating a short ''a'' {{IPAchar|/a/}}. If the Arabic letters {{m|ar|ا}} (&lrm;{{m|ar|أَلِف}}) or {{m|ar|ى}} (&lrm;{{m|ar|أَلِف مَقْصُورَة}}) immediately follow, it indicates a long ''ā'' {{IPAchar|/aː/}}.
